text: Monroe North is a census-designated place (CDP) in Snohomish County, Washington, United States. The population was 1,666 at the 2010 census. ==Geography== Monroe North is located at (47.882534, -121.987952). According to the United States Census Bureau, the CDP has a total area of 2.44 square miles (6.3 km²), all of it land. ==References== Category:Census-designated places in Snohomish County, Washington
title: Monroe North, Washington
